!What are dungeons?

While it might seem strange to have this be the first section of the article, giving proper context is necessary for a more in depth understanding. Moving on from that, we have that the word dungeon comes from french, //dojon//, and basically refers to the strong tower found on the inner part of castle, said tower often would have a room that worked as a prison cell^^<a href="https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/dungeon">1</a>^^,often also called a dungeon. It's very different to the modern day usage of the word, so where does the modern version comes from?

The modern view of dungeons comes from the massively influential, //Dungeons & Dragons//, where a dungeon is a labyrinthic complex of rooms connected into one single "structure". Dungeons there can be both man made or natural, stacked with monsters or empty of life and filled with traps or not. Thus, it is very easy to see which one Minecraft took inspiration from.

