Not only that, but the player will likely find and raid the same dungeon several times, which means the experience can get repetitive quite fast. As a way to avoid this, all structures in the game have some level of randomness in them, be it changing interiors or variants of the same structure. As an example of this, the interior layout of woodland mansions is procedurally generated and, thus, different for every mansion^^<a href="https://minecraft.fandom.com/wiki/Woodland_Mansion#Structure">2</a>^^.

